<p>Kickstarter&rsquo;s transformed the landscape for funding creative projects, but it's also launched a new movement of fans as producers &mdash; people commissioning work from artists directly instead of waiting for artists to come to them. This is the story of XOXO, an arts &amp; technology festival that became the most-funded event on Kickstarter, and the future of fans replacing traditional labels, publishers, and studios.</p>
